>
> In a message dated 1/11/03 7:44:54 PM, freeform@... writes:
>
> << Ooooh, what's the name for that, the year that the date or your
birthday
> equals your age? >>
>
> People said "star birthday" and "golden birthday."

Golden birthday was the one I was trying to think of, I think. I just
heard of it recently, I hadn't heard of it by the time I was 20, which
would have been mine (March). Ten is a good one, too.

I hope Marty has a good party - it sounds like fun! Rain and the two teen
boys next door love playing with the boffers, I might suggest the head
thing.

Dar

<< Ooooh, what's the name for that, the year that the date or your birthday
equals your age? >>

People said "star birthday" and "golden birthday."
I hadn't ever heard of it before! Holly was two on the 2nd of November, long
ago, but didn't care. Kirby's the 29th of July; by then he might not care
either. Marty got a good one!

Sandra
